    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/02-transformer/11-ssm-and-alternatives.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: Attention is O(N^2) because it wires every token to every earlier token; the alternatives replace all-pairs wiring with a single fixed-size rolling state updated left-to-right, making cost O(N) and per-step inference O(1).; Linear attention's kernel trick is pure reassociation: computing phi(K)^T V FIRST collapses the giant N x N score matrix into a tiny r x d_v state you compute once and reuse, turning O(N^2) into O(N).; The train-parallel / infer-recurrent duality: the SAME computation has a parallel matmul form (GPU-fast during training) and an O(1)-per-step recurrent form (constant memory at inference), stitched together by the chunkwise scan (dense matmul inside a chunk, carry a low-rank state between chunks).; Sparse / sliding-window attention keeps the softmax but restricts WHICH keys each query sees (banded, block-sparse, global+local), cutting O(N^2) to O(N*W); stacking L such layers compounds the effective receptive field to ~L*W.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  linear-attention-reassociation, sparse-attention-mask-family, gated-linear-recurrence-convergence\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
